16/04/2003
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- A man who testified in the trial against several former KLA members was shot dead near Pec on Monday (14 April) by gunmen who riddled his car with bullets.
Kosovo media identified the victim as Ilir Selimaj, 22, a witness for the prosecution in the trial against five former KLA members, including the brother of Kosovo politician Ramush Haradinaj.
The five were sentenced to prison for kidnapping and killing four Albanians.
(AFP, B92, BBC, Koha Ditore - 15/04/03)
